43 class RobotTrajectoryTestFixture : public testing::Test
44 {
45 protected:
46  moveit::core::RobotModelConstPtr robot_model_;
47  moveit::core::RobotStatePtr robot_state_;
48  const std::string robot_model_name_ = "panda";
49  const std::string arm_jmg_name_ = "panda_arm";
50 
51 protected:
52  void SetUp() override
53  {
54  robot_model_ = moveit::core::loadTestingRobotModel(robot_model_name_);
55  robot_state_ = std::make_shared<moveit::core::RobotState>(robot_model_);
56  robot_state_->setToDefaultValues();
57  robot_state_->setVariableVelocity(/*index*/ 0, /*value*/ 1.0);
58  robot_state_->setVariableAcceleration(/*index*/ 0, /*value*/ -0.1);
59  robot_state_->update();
60  }
61 
62  void TearDown() override
63  {
64  }

66  void initTestTrajectory(robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr& trajectory)
67  {
68  // Init a traj
69  ASSERT_TRUE(robot_model_->hasJointModelGroup(arm_jmg_name_))
70  << "Robot model does not have group: " << arm_jmg_name_;
71 
72  trajectory = std::make_shared<robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory>(robot_model_, arm_jmg_name_);
73 
74  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory->getGroupName(), arm_jmg_name_) << "Generated trajectory group name does not match";
75  EXPECT_TRUE(trajectory->empty()) << "Generated trajectory not empty";
76 
77  double duration_from_previous = 0.1;
78  std::size_t waypoint_count = 5;
79  for (std::size_t ix = 0; ix < waypoint_count; ++ix)
80  trajectory->addSuffixWayPoint(*robot_state_, duration_from_previous);
81  // Quick check that getDuration is working correctly
82  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory->getDuration(), duration_from_previous * waypoint_count)
83  << "Generated trajectory duration incorrect";
84  EXPECT_EQ(waypoint_count, trajectory->getWayPointDurations().size())
85  << "Generated trajectory has the wrong number of waypoints";
86  }
87 
88  void copyTrajectory(const robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr& trajectory,
89  robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr& trajectory_copy, bool deepcopy)
90  {
91  // Copy the trajectory
92  trajectory_copy = std::make_shared<robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory>(*trajectory, deepcopy);
93  // Quick check that the getDuration values match
94  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory_copy->getDuration(), trajectory->getDuration());
95  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory_copy->getWayPointDurations().size(), trajectory->getWayPointDurations().size());
96  }
97 
98  void modifyFirstWaypointPtrAndCheckTrajectory(robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr& trajectory)
99  {
101  // Get the first waypoint by POINTER, modify it, and check that the value WAS updated in trajectory
103  // Get the first waypoint by shared pointer
104  moveit::core::RobotStatePtr trajectory_first_waypoint = trajectory->getWayPointPtr(0);
105  // Get the first waypoint joint values
106  std::vector<double> trajectory_first_state;
107  trajectory_first_waypoint->copyJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_, trajectory_first_state);
108 
109  // Modify the first waypoint joint values
110  trajectory_first_state[0] += 0.01;
111  trajectory_first_waypoint->setJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_, trajectory_first_state);
112 
113  // Check that the trajectory's first waypoint was updated
114  moveit::core::RobotStatePtr trajectory_first_waypoint_after_update = trajectory->getWayPointPtr(0);
115  std::vector<double> trajectory_first_state_after_update;
116  trajectory_first_waypoint_after_update->copyJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_, trajectory_first_state_after_update);
117  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory_first_state[0], trajectory_first_state_after_update[0]);
118  }
119 
120  void modifyFirstWaypointAndCheckTrajectory(robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr& trajectory)
121  {
123  // Get the first waypoint by VALUE, modify it, and check that the value WAS NOT updated in trajectory
125  // Get the first waypoint by shared pointer
126  moveit::core::RobotState trajectory_first_waypoint = trajectory->getWayPoint(0);
127  // Get the first waypoint joint values
128  std::vector<double> trajectory_first_state;
129  trajectory_first_waypoint.copyJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_, trajectory_first_state);
130 
131  // Modify the first waypoint joint values
132  trajectory_first_state[0] += 0.01;
133  trajectory_first_waypoint.setJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_, trajectory_first_state);
134 
135  // Check that the trajectory's first waypoint was updated
136  moveit::core::RobotState trajectory_first_waypoint_after_update = trajectory->getWayPoint(0);
137  std::vector<double> trajectory_first_state_after_update;
138  trajectory_first_waypoint_after_update.copyJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_, trajectory_first_state_after_update);
139  EXPECT_NE(trajectory_first_state[0], trajectory_first_state_after_update[0]);
140  }
141 };

157 TEST_F(RobotTrajectoryTestFixture, DoubleReverse)
158 {
159  robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr trajectory;
160  initTestTrajectory(trajectory);
161  moveit_msgs::RobotTrajectory initial_trajectory_msg;
162  trajectory->getRobotTrajectoryMsg(initial_trajectory_msg);
163 
164  trajectory->reverse().reverse();
165 
166  moveit_msgs::RobotTrajectory edited_trajectory_msg;
167  trajectory->getRobotTrajectoryMsg(edited_trajectory_msg);
168 
169  EXPECT_EQ(initial_trajectory_msg, edited_trajectory_msg);
170 }

172 TEST_F(RobotTrajectoryTestFixture, ChainEdits)
173 {
174  robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr initial_trajectory;
175  initTestTrajectory(initial_trajectory);
176  moveit_msgs::RobotTrajectory initial_trajectory_msg;
177  initial_trajectory->getRobotTrajectoryMsg(initial_trajectory_msg);
178 
179  robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory trajectory(robot_model_);
180  trajectory.setGroupName(arm_jmg_name_)
181  .clear()
182  .setRobotTrajectoryMsg(*robot_state_, initial_trajectory_msg)
183  .reverse()
184  .addSuffixWayPoint(*robot_state_, 0.1)
185  .addPrefixWayPoint(*robot_state_, 0.1)
186  .insertWayPoint(1, *robot_state_, 0.1)
187  .append(*initial_trajectory, 0.1);
188 
189  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory.getGroupName(), arm_jmg_name_);
190  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory.getWayPointCount(), initial_trajectory->getWayPointCount() * 2 + 3);
191 }

193 TEST_F(RobotTrajectoryTestFixture, RobotTrajectoryShallowCopy)
194 {
195  bool deepcopy = false;
196 
197  robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr trajectory;
198  robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectoryPtr trajectory_copy;
199 
200  initTestTrajectory(trajectory);
201  copyTrajectory(trajectory, trajectory_copy, deepcopy);
202  modifyFirstWaypointPtrAndCheckTrajectory(trajectory);
203 
204  // Check that modifying the waypoint also modified the trajectory
205  moveit::core::RobotState trajectory_first_waypoint_after_update = trajectory->getWayPoint(0);
206  std::vector<double> trajectory_first_state_after_update;
207  trajectory_first_waypoint_after_update.copyJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_, trajectory_first_state_after_update);
208 
209  // Get the first waypoint in the modified trajectory_copy
210  moveit::core::RobotState trajectory_copy_first_waypoint_after_update = trajectory_copy->getWayPoint(0);
211  std::vector<double> trajectory_copy_first_state_after_update;
212  trajectory_copy_first_waypoint_after_update.copyJointGroupPositions(arm_jmg_name_,
213  trajectory_copy_first_state_after_update);
214 
215  // Check that we updated the value correctly in the trajectory
216  EXPECT_EQ(trajectory_first_state_after_update[0], trajectory_copy_first_state_after_update[0]);
217 }

234 
235  // Get the first waypoint in the modified trajectory_copy

237  std::vector<double> trajectory_copy_first_state_after_update;
